[T63] [tier:2] Shipped full database backup/restore capability. Backend: GET /admin/db/backup dumps all 4 MongoDB collections (users, tournaments, games, teams) as timestamped JSON download with Content-Disposition header. POST /admin/db/restore accepts multipart form upload of that JSON, validates source signature, and replaces all data while preserving the requesting admin account to prevent lockout. Frontend: new Database Backup & Restore glassmorphism card in Admin Controls tab with amber-gradient Download button, hidden file input for Restore, and danger-confirmation dialog via the existing confirm() pattern. Pushed to origin/main for Railway redeploy.
[T65] [tier:2] Shipped tournament schedule management feature. Backend: PUT /admin/tournament/schedule endpoint handles cancel_day_index (adds to cancelled_dates array, deletes orphaned games/teams) and add_date (appends to dates[], re-sorts chronologically). Frontend: Admin lifecycle day tabs now show MM/DD format with cancelled days greyed+strikethrough, cancel XCircle buttons on future days with danger confirmation, and a + button that opens native date picker for adding days (auto-submits on selection). Downstream effects handled: Grand Reveal gating skips cancelled indices, backup day selector hides cancelled days, player attendance planner hides cancelled days. Architecture decision: used cancelled_dates marking (Option A) instead of re-indexing to preserve day_index stability across games and teams collections.
[T67] [tier:2] Shipped player game history modal feature. Backend: GET /admin/users/<id>/game-history endpoint returns all finalized games for a player sorted by day/round, with partner names, opponent names, player score, opponent score, win/loss/tie result, and running total points. Also returns a summary object with total_points, wins, losses, ties, games_played. Frontend: Clicking a player name in the Global Roster (now teal colored and clickable) opens a glassmorphism modal with Framer Motion animation. Modal displays four summary stat cards (total pts, wins, losses, games) and a full game-by-game table with columns for Day, Round, Partner, Opponents, Score (color-coded), Result (W/L/T badge), and Running Total. Power player solo games show zap Solo in partner column. Modal closes on backdrop click or X button.
[T70] [tier:2] Fixed critical tournament day 1 check-in bug. The scheduler is_checkin_window_open function queried for tournaments with status [active, blackout] but missed upcoming. On the first tournament day, before admin transitions status, the tournament is still upcoming — so players got No active tournament today when trying to check in. Added upcoming to the scheduler query to match the Tournament.find_active pattern. One-line fix, committed and pushed to Railway.
[T72] [tier:2] Fixed critical production API URL routing bug. The frontend config.js relied on VITE_API_URL being baked in at build time, but nixpacks on Railway was not injecting it. The fallback was http://${window.location.hostname}:5001, which resolves to http://www.bagsandbrats.com:5001 in production — a dead endpoint. All API calls (register, login, check-in) silently failed. Fix: added production detection in config.js that auto-detects non-localhost environments and uses the Railway backend URL (bagsbrats-production.up.railway.app) directly. Local dev still falls back to localhost:5001.
[T74] [tier:2] Shipped admin inline player editing. Backend PUT /admin/users/:id now accepts email with duplicate detection (prevents auth collisions). Frontend AdminUserManagement.jsx gained a pencil icon per row that opens a glassmorphic edit modal with name/email/phone fields. Saves via the existing endpoint. Follows the existing modal pattern (same as player history modal). Pushed to Railway.
[T76] [tier:2] Shipped surgical player swap on game cards. Backend POST /admin/games/:id now accepts team1_player_ids and team2_player_ids with player validation. Frontend AdminGameManagement.jsx gained a purple Swap button per game card that opens a two-column modal with Team 1 and Team 2 dropdowns populated from the full player roster. Works on any game status (upcoming/active/finalized) for ad-hoc corrections during live tournament play.
[T78] [tier:2] Fixed critical score swap bug for Team 2 players. The PlayerDashboard UI dynamically swaps team names so Your Team is always on the left and Opponents on the right. But score submission always sent the left input as score1 and right input as score2 — where score1 in the database is always Team 1s score. When a Team 2 player submitted, their teams score got saved as Team 1s score, silently swapping the results. Fix: detect which team the submitter is on and swap score1/score2 before sending to the API. Also fixed the finalized score display so Team 2 players see the correct score under their team name.
[T80] [tier:2] Fixed date-aware tournament day detection across the entire stack. Backend /tournaments/active now returns is_tournament_day boolean and today date. Player check-in card hidden on non-tournament days with next-game-day info. Admin day tabs use date comparison (not index) for past/current/future coloring. Big Reveal disabled on non-tournament days. Also split Full Name into First Name / Last Name across registration, admin edit, proxy register, and user settings with backward-compatible computed name field.
